President Trump visited Lake Okeechobee in Florida to highlight the success of a construction project aimed at addressing the lake's problems. He thanked Governor DeSantis, Senator Rubio, and other officials for their support in securing funding for the project. The President also discussed the importance of addressing water quality issues in Florida and expressed his commitment to protecting the Everglades. In addition, he spoke about the immigration crisis and the possibility of closing the southern border if Mexico does not take action to stop illegal immigration. The President also mentioned his administration's efforts to improve healthcare and lower costs for Americans.